17 WHEREAS, this outstanding team has completed another championship season football
18 competition by posting an outstanding record of 13 wins and only one loss, marking the fifth
19 time in program history of winning 13 or more games in a season; and
20 WHEREAS, this season also marked the team's 20th appearance in the NCAA post-season,
21 the 34 post-season victories are the fourth-most all-time in Division II; and
22
23 WHEREAS, the football team has now had five different Blazer head coaches reach the
24 NCAA title game, marking the most number of coaches reaching the championship at one
25 school in Division II history; and
26 WHEREAS, the phenomenal performance of the 2024 season saw the team go undefeated
27 in league play for the sixth time in program history, finished the season with five
28 All-America selections, and recognized quarterback Sammy Edwards as a finalist for the
29 prestigious Harlon Hill Award for the second-straight year; and
30 WHEREAS, the Blazer football team now stands at 346 victories with 138 defeats and four
31 ties in 42 playing seasons of football, with the 2024 team posting the 15th season of
32 double-digit victories in program history; and
33 WHEREAS, as this magnificent team earned its well-deserved reputation for excellence by
34 performing with courage and precision over months of training and competition, it is
35 abundantly proper to call them champions.
36 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
37 congratulate the Valdosta State University football team for winning the 2024 Gulf South
